        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:11PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Dillon, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon and Beaverhead Rock State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
